ereas in America all three forms of the name are approximately equally common.  See also  Alun ."]},{"name":"Albert","meanings":["From an Old French name, <i>Albert</i>, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>adal</i> ‘noble’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England, displacing the Old English form <i>Æþelbeorht</i>. The name is popular in a variety of forms in Western Europe, and has been traditional in a number of European princely families. It was out of favour in England for centuries, however, and the revival of its popularity in the 19th century was largely in honour of  Queen Victoria's  consort,  Prince Albert of Saxe-Coburg-Gotha ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Dafydd ap Rhys was born about 1304, in Carmarthenshire, Wales, United Kingdom as the son of Rhys Ap Gwilym. He had at least 1 son with Mrs. Dafydd ap Rhys."},"et":{"about 1304–":"umbes 1304–Surnud","1304–Male":"1304–Surnud","1308–Female":"1308–Surnud","1330–Male":"1330–Surnud","1270–Male":"1270–Surnud","1304":"1304","about 1304":"umbes 1304","1330":"1330","about 1330":"umbes 1330","1270":"1270","1308":"1308","of,Cedweli cmt,Carmarthenshire,Wales":"Carmarthenshire, Wales, United Kingdom","{Lln ap Gwrgan}":"Ascoli Piceno, Marche, Itaalia","Kidwelly, Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Kidwelly, Carmarthenshire, Wales"},"fi":{"about 1304–":"noin 1304–Kuollut","1304–Male":"1304–Kuollut","1308–Female":"1308–Kuollut","1330–Male":"1330–Kuollut","1270–Male":"1270–Kuollut","1304":"1304","about 1304":"noin 1304","1330":"1330","about 1330":"noin 1330","1270":"1270","1308":"1308","of,Cedweli cmt,Carmarthenshire,Wales":"Carmarthenshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","{Lln ap Gwrgan}":"Ascoli Piceno, Marche, Italia","Kidwelly, Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Kidwelly, Carmarthenshire, Wales"},"fr":{"about 1304–":"environ 1304–Décédé","1304–Male":"1304–Décédé","1308–Female":"1308–Décédée","1330–Male":"1330–Décédé","1270–Male":"1270–Décédé","1304":"1304","about 1304":"enviro